14
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:58,900
<i>We're good with not getting physical, right?</i>

15
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:01,610
<i>Our relationship's not like that.</i>

16
00:01:05,650 --> 00:01:08,830
Faking our kiss at the altar?
What are we, actors in a movie?

17
00:01:08,830 --> 00:01:12,520
No, even actors go further than that.

18
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:18,230
<i>Getting physical with Ouji.
I'd never thought about it before.</i>

19
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:21,810
But once a couple marries,
don't they normally...

20
00:01:28,450 --> 00:01:30,170
<i>What's wrong?</i>

21
00:01:31,450 --> 00:01:36,580
<i>I thought you'd never...</i>

22
00:01:37,230 --> 00:01:39,420
<i>do this sort of thing with me.</i>

23
00:01:41,620 --> 00:01:43,380
<i>Dummy.</i>

24
00:01:46,830 --> 00:01:48,290
<i>No, I...</i>

25
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:52,980
<i>I was saving it for our first night together.</i>

26
00:02:02,410 --> 00:02:07,640
<i>Your voice. It's cute.</i>

27
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:16,000
Haru?

28
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,050
Earth to Haru.

29
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:22,170
Did you hear a word we said?

30
00:02:22,170 --> 00:02:24,220
- I am so sorry.
- Jeez...

31
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:27,050
Still getting lost in your thoughts, I see.

32
00:02:27,050 --> 00:02:28,830
I'm so embarrassed...

33
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:32,710
How do you two know each other?

34
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:34,480
He's a graphic designer, and I'm a writer.

35
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:36,140
If I had to put a word to it, we're...

36
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:40,880
Old partners. They used to work together
back when they were rookies.

37
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,940
You'd daydream back then, too?

38
00:02:42,940 --> 00:02:44,730
Enough about me.

39
00:02:44,730 --> 00:02:47,200
